SectionBody.Text: The board shall set fees according to the following schedule:

Subsection.Text: The fee for application or certification pursuant to ss. 459.0055(2), 459.0075, and 459.0077 shall not exceed $500.

The fee for application and examination pursuant to s. 459.0055(1)(m) shall not exceed $175 plus the actual per applicant cost to the department for purchase of the examination from the National Board of Osteopathic Medical Examiners or a similar national organization.
The fee for biennial renewal of licensure or certification shall not exceed $500.
